<div class="row">
    <h3 class="text-center">Andriod Setup</h3>
    <h4 class="text-center">Main Menu</h4>
    <img src="img/information_page/ventriloid-mainmenu.PNG" class="img-responsive img-grounded img-center" alt="ventriloid-mainmenu.PNG" usemap="#ventriloid-map" />
    <map name="ventriloid-map" id="ventriloid-map">
        <area alt="ventriloid-logo-coords" title="ventriloid Logo" href="#" shape="poly" coords="44,44,44,6,6,5,9,40" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="left" />
        <area alt="ventriloid-servername-coords" title="Server Display Name" href="#" shape="poly" coords="50,6,55,56,302,62,293,7" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="bottom" />
        <area alt="ventriloid-connectbtn-coords" title="Connect to Server Button" href="#" shape="poly" coords="323,41,350,40,351,10,322,9" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="right" />
        <area alt="ventriloid-developer-coords" title="Developer's Credits and Donation" href="#" shape="poly" coords="10,579,57,581,55,616,8,617" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="right" />
        <area alt="ventriloid-appsetting-coords" title="ventriloid Phone Application Settings" href="#" shape="poly" coords="304,579,356,575,356,613,315,615" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="left" />
    </map>
    <h4 class="text-center">Manage Servers</h4>
    <img src="img/information_page/ventriloid-manageservers.PNG" class="img-responsive img-grounded img-center" alt="ventriloid-manageserver.PNG" />
    <p><b>Manage Servers:</b> Click the Plus sign to add credentials to connect to a specific server. To connecto MPC, click on this <a href="#connectventrilo">link</a>, and then click "connect". The Icon next is the trash can to delete servers you no longer want to remember. A List will populate here as the second server will appear below MPC in the example of the image above.</p>
    <h4 class="text-center">Add Server</h4>
    <img src="img/information_page/ventriloid-addserver.PNG" class="img-responsive img-grounded img-center" alt="ventriloid-addserver.PNG" />
    <p><b>Add Server:</b> This is where you put the information regarding the server you're trying to connect to. <b>User Name</b> is your username when you join this server.<b>Phonetic</b> is what other users will hear when YOU join the server, or a channel.<b>Server Name</b> is only what YOU see this server in the <b>manage servers</b> section.<b>Hostname</b> this is either an IP Address(192.192.192.111 in example), or a domain name (lead.typefrag.com) that allows you to connect to a server.<b>Port</b> this is a four digit number to connect to the the server, and if the numbers are not correct the connection will disconnect with a timed out error message.<b>Password</b> some servers are security protected, or private with password requirements.</p>
    <h4 class="text-center">Developer Credits</h4>
    <p>These are credits made by Ventrilo's Mobile Design Staff's Team. If you like the service they've done, please donate to them.</p>
    <h4 class="text-center">Phone Application Settings</h4>
    <p>General Setting</p>
    <ul class="list-group">
        <li class="list-group-item">Keep Screen On(Drains battery, but when signed on to ventriloid doesn't dim.)</li>
        <li class="list-group-item">Notifications(This controls ventrilo's preference notification response. Eligble to silent, ringtone, or "Text-to-speech" responses.)</li>
        <li class="list-group-item">Voice Activation</li>
        <li class="list-group-item">Character Encoding(Changes languages for the software.)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Push to Talk Setting</p>
    <ul class="list-group">
        <li class="list-group-item">Push to Talk Toggle(This turns your voice button to click to speak, then click again to turn off the speaking capability.)</li>
        <li class="list-group-item">Enable Push to Talk Hardware(Allows you to select a button physically on the phone such as volume buttons, camera, frontside buttons on the phone to use as a speaking button. Only works when application is up.)</li>
        <li class="list-group-item">Set Push to Talk Key(Only works when previous description is enabled."Push to Talk Hardware" is check marked.)</li>
        <li class="list-group-item">Push to Talk Vibrate(This enables vibration everytime you push the button down to speak.)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Text To Speech</p>
    <p>This is the voice that speaks outloud when:</p>
    <ul class="list-group">
        <li class="list-group-item">Connected(When you Sign on.)</li>
        <li class="list-group-item">Disconnected(When  you Signed off.)</li>
        <li class="list-group-item">User Log In / Log Out(When someone else Signs on or off.)</li>
        <li class="list-group-item">User Joins / Leaves Channel(When you, or someone else, join or leave(s) a channel on the server.)</li>
        <li class="list-group-item">Page Recieved(Pages is when someone send a noise indicating like a simple tap on the shoulder with no message.)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>After that, the rest of the settings for notifications is the sound the phone will make when that action is performed by the application.</p>
</div>
